# INSTALL INSTRUCTIONS

## General idea

Go to the build directory and use the usual cmake commands to configure and build

---

## Required Packages

Packages needed : 

*(apt names)*
```
gcc g++ make cmake sdl2 sdl2-image sdl2-ttf libsdl2-dev libsdl2-image-dev libsdl2-ttf-dev libXrandr-dev ... zenity
```

*(pacman names)* 
```
gcc g++ make cmake ... zenity
```

*(dnf names)* 
```
gcc g++ make cmake SDL2 SDL2-devel SDL2_image SDL2_image-devel SDL2_ttf SDL2_ttf-devel ... zenity
```

*(Windows : dll & dev libs)*
```
SDL2 SDL2-Image SDL2-ttf 
```

---

## Install commands

```
cd build
cmake ..
cmake --build .
../test
```

*Shorter version*
```
cd build
cmake .. && cmake --build . && ../test
```
